---
title: Button Group
---

p.-text
  | Button groups are used to wrap a series of buttons on a single line.

h3 Examples
h4 Base
p.-text To render a button group, wrap a series of buttons in a div and apply the class <code>m-btnGroup</code>.
.example.-mb--3
  .-p--3
    .m-btnGroup
      button(class=`a-btn`) Button
      button(class=`a-btn`) Button
      button(class=`a-btn`) Button
  :code(lang='html')
    <div class="m-btnGroup">
      <button class="a-btn">Button</button>
      <button class="a-btn">Button</button>
      <button class="a-btn">Button</button>
    </div>

h4 Vertical
p.-text To render a series of buttons vertically, apply the class modifier <code>-vertical</code>.
.example.-mb--3
  .-p--3
    .m-btnGroup.-vertical
      button(class=`a-btn`) Button
      button(class=`a-btn`) Button
      button(class=`a-btn`) Button
  :code(lang='html')
    <div class="m-btnGroup -vertical">
      <button class="a-btn">Button</button>
      <button class="a-btn">Button</button>
      <button class="a-btn">Button</button>
    </div>

h4 Pill
p.-text Use the <code>-pill</code> modifier class to render a series of buttons with a more pronounced border-radius.
.example.-mb--3
  .-p--3
    .m-btnGroup.-pill
      button(class=`a-btn`) Button
      button(class=`a-btn`) Button
      button(class=`a-btn`) Button
  :code(lang='html')
